	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104397035953896><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=4066&mid=104397035953896>nother epic question</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=4066&mid=104397035953896#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=201427><span id= >thebeavergrind</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>16 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 30th 7:15 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sucessfully pick pocketed both tani and founy with relative ease, tho had trouble with tani, he aggroed 2 times, but made it out safely. My question is: What is the best way to get the book of souls? im about to join a 45+ guild, but my friend said they can raid it, but not with ease. Am i going to have to solo? thanx to all for answers.<br><br>Daillan Shadowrunner<br>Halfling Rogue of the 42nd season<br>Servant of Bristlebane<br>Tunare server<br><br>&quot;Look not to others for knowledge, for this is your story too.&quot;&nbsp;&nbsp;-Auron<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=104479996866774></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104479996866774><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=4066&mid=104479996866774>RE: nother epic question</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=4066&mid=104479996866774#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=121023><span id= >kenlaan</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>2 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Feb 9th 9:43 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I got it solo. It's not *that* hard, but it can get scary. Best thing to do is get the stone you need to get ported there (sold in Neriak Cleric guild, forget its exact name.. then get someone to killl you in an arena area, such as the one in West Freeport. This allows you to have the full 3 hour rez timer without losing exp. Have a Cleric somewhat ready to give you some sort of raise, after you grab the Book. After that, either get a very brave Wizard to port you in there and immediately gate out from your guild, or pay someone. The truth is that there's zero danger in the port-in area. The moment you step out, that's another thing. I had to pay my ride 700p before he agreed.<br><br>Upon entering, immediately sneak hide, get out of the building, and hand a right. You'll hit the wall, which is very near by. Make another right, and follow the wall basically the whole way. At this point you can use the map from eqatlas.com. <br><br>When I went, I made it, but the book wasn't there. I had to camp so my raise timer didn't drop down. Nothing was in the room with me at the time. I logged back in two hours later, no book, no mob.. the second time, book was there, as well as a mob that I'm surprised didn't see me. Anyway, once you grab the book, get your Cleric to raise you, and you're done with that step. <br><br>Just con *everything.* Liches will be your main problem. They can see invisible, but can't detect you when sneaking behind them. Other than that, I didn't come across anything that could see me.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
