	   <tr><td colspan=2>That's a tough question.&nbsp;&nbsp;A lot of people say get the fastest weapon you can, which is a good idea, others stress a lot of stats, I got for a little of both using a Blood Point for the extra SVdis and STR and a nice 21 Delay and extremely helpful proc.  With 5k, you could get a nice weapon of about any kind.   Obviously though, you're not going to be able to buy a better mainhand than your epic with 5k, so stick with that.  For offhand, it's probably best now to use another piercer, whereas before 50 it's usually best to use a 1hs or 1hb offhand (piercing has a slight advantage over slashing and blunt, about 5-10 skill points), but that's really up to you.<br><br>With that in mind, here's a few options.  Prices might be out of your 5k range, but servers vary HEAVILY on prices, as you probably know.<br><br>Piercers<br>--------<br>Fester<br>Sebilite Croaking Dirk<br>Stone Bladed Edge<br>Crescent Blades of Luclin<br>Shadowy Dirk <br><br>If you wanna go with a 1hs,<br>1hs<br>---<br>Bone Handled Scimitar<br>Jagged Blade of Mourning (good and very cheap)<br>Tae Ew Bloodletter's Sword<br><br>There's always more, but hey, there's a few good ideas.<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>-----------------------<br>Rogues do it from behind.<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105276" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105276</a> <br>Tyrlinoth Arkonnen &lt;Purgatory&gt; - The Nameless</td></tr>
