	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103704341230630><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=4066&mid=103704341230630>RE: Weapons....</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=4066&mid=103704341230630#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=125152><span id= >Rollander</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>348 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 11th 2:57 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.72]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Don't offhand your Ragebringer until you get something in the same damage range as it.&nbsp;&nbsp;For example, if you were to find a weapon that were, say, 14/18, I'd put that primary because the extra backstab damage you'd get from the RB won't be seen to a great extent, whereas the highspeed of your 14/18 will really kick ass.<br><br>That 10/18 should go offhand because in main, you won't do that much damage in your backstabs.  Your backstab damage is a function of the weapons damage, (10 in this case, 15 in the case of the RB) so you would expect the ragebringer to backstab ROUGHLY 1.5x higher than the 10 damage.<br><br>In my case, I was using a 10/21 main before epic and hitting right near 300 for backstabs at level 54.  After my 15/25 epic, I've been hitting in the mid 400s and I doubt I've hit my max yet.<br><br>Rogue weapons are a pain because of this backstab rule.  We do NOT get any weapons above 16 damage because the backstab damage would just be too high and all the wizzy's would complain because we'd do more damage than their best DDs.  For instance: <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=16986" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=16986</a><br><br>A 20/26 Piercer, but Rogues can't use it.  <br><br>Bloodbath and Khalshazar are the only 16 damage ROGUE piercers out there.  Ragebringer is one of about 14 others in the 15/x range.<br><br>OK, so here's the thing.  Keep that Epic main until you find something with EQUAL damage that is faster 15/24, 15/23, whatever, OR find a 14 Damage piercer that is exceedingly faster (Windspeeder 14/18!)  I can't think of any other reason to NOT use Ragebringer in main, except maybe if the weapon had an unstoppable beyond-cool proc?<br><br>The other reason is that you've got 2 weapons that are better than your epic AND you have another haste item that can match or exceed Seething Fury (such as Broken Drive Belt)<br><br>EDIT<br>New top dog rogue weapon <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=17087" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=17087</a> Dart of Immobility.  Look for it in your dreams!<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Nov 13 23:06:30 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>-----------------------<br>Rogues do it from behind.<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105276" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105276</a> <br>Tyrlinoth Arkonnen &lt;Purgatory&gt; - The Nameless</td></tr>
