	   <tr><td colspan=2>I got my pieces on the first visit to each city, with 198 Pickpocket skill. I guess I was lucky =)<br>Anyways, what I did for Tani N'Mar was get teh /loc of him by standing right next to him, then I went onto the roof of the Rogue guild and went to that same /loc (except the 3rd #, obviously), keeping Tani targetted.&nbsp;&nbsp;Then I PPed away and got it after about 16 times mashing the hotkey. Now, this way is better because you can get away if he attacks you; DIRECTLY after you hit PickPocket each time, you con Tani. If he goes to Threatheningly, you run real fast to the zone. By DIRECTLY after, I mean you should almost make the click of you PP key and the click of teh &quot;C&quot; button on your keyboard sound as one. This is, IMO, the safest way to PP the Stained Parchment Bottom.<br>As for Founy, I suppose if you were real paranoid that he was going to attack you, you could go below him in the mines or something and have a TPer there with TL: Bind memmed and ready to go, and you could do sorta the same thing.<br>Good luck with your epic quest.<br><br>-Thommus Slighthand<br>Hobbit Thief of the 46th Vial<br>&lt;Hand of Mana&gt; THe Nameless Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
